dcterms:description: A two-dimensional environment where navigation unfolds within a flat plane, characterized by dimensions of 50 units each, with a start position at (0, 0) and a goal position at (49, 49). The agent can take four possible actions (up, down, left, right) and undergoes training over 500 episodes with a maximum of 20,000 steps per episode.
dcterms:title: Two-Dimensional Environment

dcterms:description: A three-dimensional environment that accommodates movement in three dimensions, with dimensions of 50 units each for width, height, and depth. The start position is at (0, 0, 0) and the goal position is at (49, 49, 49). The agent can take six possible actions (up, down, left, right, forward, backward) and undergoes training over 5,000 episodes with a maximum of 20,000 steps per episode.
dcterms:title: Three-Dimensional Environment
